# ==============================================================================
# PRETTIER EXCLUSION RULES
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Tells Prettier which paths to skip so formatting only runs on
# human-authored files and avoids generated or vendor-managed artifacts.
# Docs: https://prettier.io/docs/ignore
# ==============================================================================

# ==========================================
# VCS & DEPENDENCIES
# ==========================================
# Why: Git internals and third-party packages should never be formatted.
# Default: Prettier includes files unless matched by ignore rules.
# Use Case: Prevents unnecessary work and accidental changes in external files.
.git
node_modules

# ==========================================
# BUILD OUTPUTS
# ==========================================
# Why: Build directories are generated and can be safely regenerated.
# Default: Included during broad format runs like `prettier --write .`.
# Use Case: Keeps formatting focused on source files developers maintain.
dist
out
lib/scripts

# ==========================================
# STATIC GENERATED ASSETS
# ==========================================
# Why: Static output folders may contain minified or machine-produced files.
# Default: Included in recursive formatting scans.
# Use Case: Avoids touching assets that should remain byte-stable.
public/static
